Read the data .CSV files of adults arrest in DC area from 2016-2021

df_2016<-data.frame(read.csv("Arrests 2016 Public.csv"))[,1:14]
df_2017<-data.frame(read.csv("Arrests 2017 Public.csv"))[,1:14]
df_2018<-data.frame(read.csv("Arrests by Year, 2018.csv"))[,1:14]
df_2019<-data.frame(read.csv("Arrests by Year, 2019.csv"))[,1:14]
df_2020<-data.frame(read.csv("Arrests by Year 2020.csv"))[,1:14]
df_2021<-data.frame(read.csv("2021 Adult Arrests.csv"))[,1:14]

Note that the colnames of df_2016 and df_2017 are not the same with others. But those indices are just about arrest location which is not what we are investigating. Therefore I just combined them by the same indices that we need. (A-N columns) ##Merge Multiple CSV Files bind by rows

DF<-rbind(df_2016,df_2017,df_2018,df_2019,df_2020,df_2021)

find NaN

sum_age<-sum(is.nan(DF$Age))
sum_year<-sum(is.nan(DF$Arrest.Year))
sum_race<-sum(is.nan(DF$Defendant.Race))
sum_sex<-sum(is.nan(DF$Defendant.Sex))
sum_category<-sum(is.nan(DF$Arrest.Category))
sum_nan<-sum_age+sum_race+sum_sex+sum_category+sum_year
sum_nan

The top several crime among “white(and black)” males of every year is 2016 Simple Assault, Release Violations/Fugitive, Traffic Violations, Narcotics, Theft, Other Crimes`

2017 Simple Assault, Release Violations/Fugitive, Traffic Violations, Narcotics, Other Crimes, Theft

2018 Simple Assault, Release Violations/Fugitive, Traffic Violations, Narcotics, Theft, Other Crimes

2019 Simple Assault, Traffic Violations, Release Violations/Fugitive, Narcotics, Theft, Other Crimes

2020 Simple Assault, Release Violations/Fugitive, Traffic Violations, Weapon Violations, Narcotics, Other Crimes

2021 Simple Assault, Release Violations/Fugitive (Warr), Weapon Violations, Traffic Violations, Other Crimes, Driving/Boating While Intoxicated
